---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config/site';
---
<Layout
  title={`AI-assisted Content Disclosure | ${SITE.name}`}
  description="Disclosure of how Compute Current uses AI-assisted tools for source review, categorization, summarization, drafting, and editorial checks."
  canonicalPath="/ai-disclosure/"
>
  <main class="policy-shell">
    <a class="back-link" href="/">Latest analysis</a>
    <article class="policy-page">
      <p class="eyebrow">AI-assisted Disclosure</p>
      <h1>AI assists the workflow. Source facts set the boundary.</h1>
      <p class="policy-lede">
        Compute Current uses AI-assisted systems to help process source reporting into infrastructure intelligence. We use those systems as editorial tooling, not as a replacement for source attribution or quality controls.
      </p>

      <section>
        <h2>Where AI May Be Used</h2>
        <p>
          AI may assist with source review, coverage categorization, summarization, headline options, draft generation, repetition checks, and editorial review.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Where AI Is Constrained</h2>
        <p>
          Generated analysis must use source-specific facts. If the source is incomplete or the item lacks a concrete infrastructure angle, Compute Current avoids turning it into long-form analysis.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>How Readers Can Verify</h2>
        <p>
          Article pages display source attribution and link to the original report. Compute Current keeps its own URL for its analysis while making the original reporting easy to verify.
        </p>
      </section>

      <nav class="policy-link-row" aria-label="Transparency pages">
        <a href="/about/">About</a>
        <a href="/editorial-policy/">Editorial Policy</a>
        <a href="/methodology/">Methodology</a>
      </nav>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
